            "Most of what separates flat food from delicious food comes down to four elements. Salt amplifies flavor and suppresses bitterness; most home food is under-salted. Fat carries flavor and creates richness and texture. Acid - vinegar, citrus, wine - brightens and balances richness. Heat (both temperature and chili) shapes texture and adds another dimension.",
            "Seasoning is not a single step at the end; it is a series of adjustments throughout cooking, tasting as you go. When a dish tastes 'off' but you cannot name why, run through the four: does it need salt, fat, acid, or heat? Usually one of them is the answer, and acid is the most commonly missing."
