            "Develop a vocabulary for what is wrong: flat (needs salt), heavy (needs acid), thin (needs fat or reduction), harsh (needs cooking time or sweetness), one-note (needs contrast or a finishing element). Adjusting is a loop - taste, diagnose, adjust, taste - that you run until the dish is balanced."
